caption: The most friendly place in NE. The service here is a reflection of the neighborhood, everyone that walks by smiles and greets each other. Patio dining is available. The portions were large and everything was very tasty. BYOB from the shop nextdoor to enjoy with your meal. Highly recommend.

Great food! I feel bad for anyone who haven’t had their food. You don’t know what you’re missing. Seriously tho.

Best BBQ in Mass and this is coming from a girl who grew up in Texas. Mouth watering bbq and the customer service is top notch. I had the pulled pork dinner with sweet potato fries and baked beans and my boyfriend had the ribs. The ribs fell off the bone and the pulled pork tasted like love. Everyone should try this place.

We had dinner on the patio with our dog. Service was excellent and they spoiled our pup. Great hidden gem and it’s byob . Everything was delicious. We even got two cheeseburger sliders for our dog . Great pulled pork , bbq chicken , Mac n cheese, sweet potato fries , corn bread . Liquor store on one side and frozen yogurt on the other . I think they should heat the patio to keep it open longer .
Drove through half a foot of snow to pick up bbq from this place. Worth it. Delicious food and friendly staff. Will be back many times. Highly recommend.

This is a top restaurant in Worcester.  My family has been eating here since the time of opening until today, and the food is consistently delicious and craveable. We love it. We feel at home. The owners and staff always make us feel more than welcome. Kudos to the chef who developed the recipes.  When I eat out, I like to leave thinking how did they make this so delicious and they do that to me every time. The food is special and even if I tried to make it myself, it just would never be the same.  If you are in the area, this is a must.  We love it all from the Caesar salad, the ribs, rice and beans, pulled pork, to the sweet potato fries.  I would give them 100 stars if I could.

I have to say hands down some of the best BBQ EVER!!! Absolutely amazing service, super friendly, this was the best way to start off the new year. I can't say enough good things. The star rating system doesn't go high enough for this REAL BBQ restaurant, 100 stars at least.

My husband and I recently moved to the area and WS&B has been an amazing comfort for us! Their wings are some of the best we've had and are HUGE. The owner is a total sweetheart as well. Don't ignore their modest facade which is easy to miss while moving down Pleasant St. (although they're technically located on Richmond Ave). If you're looking for something tasty, give this place a shot <3

I visit this lovely place quite a bit! This is my favorite place to eat.  I go there frequently. The cooking is fantastic, the team is polite and the charge is good. I enjoy being in this spot over a decent supper.

We ordered for delivery, which is always a pain because suddenly restaurants realize they're not immediately answerable to the customer and don't have to worry about doing anything correctly it seems.  I ordered half a rack of ribs, which arrived room temperature. The meat was tough and chewy but tasted good. I don't know why people are going crazy over the cornbread, it just tasted like a dry tasteless muffin to me.  My friend ordered a medium-rare steak and it arrived well done. Do we have to order it bleu to get it medium-rare?  The food was edible and didn't make me wretch or anything but the fact its quality was so subpar and arrived cold really has put me off from ever ordering from here again.

Amazing experience.  The owner took great care of us and was warm and generous. She snuck us goodies and was knowledgeable about the area, and about life.  All the food was great quality and the meats were rich and smokey.  Will be back!

Went there with my friends, had a pleasant conversation with one of the workers. We got the $40 barbecue meal with the ribs, half chicken, and brisket with 5 sides. It was our first time having ribs and they were the star of the meal, very delicious and the BBQ sauce was amazing. The chicken was decent. The brisket was a huge disappointment, although it was tender it was also bland, tasteless, and also unappealing, almost like it was boiled.  For the sides we got rice and beans (subpar), corn and beans (average but enjoyable), baked potato (nothing special, just a potato that’s baked), onion rings (crispy, golden, and delicious), and lastly Macaroni and cheese (basically Kraft powder cheese sauce, enjoyable)  Overall I really enjoyed our visit, the ribs is the reason we’re going back. We are going to try some different dishes this time. If Ribs are what you’re looking for, highly recommend this place, brisket not so much.

So I just moved back to Massachusetts from down south and have had a craving for some real BBQ. Googled best BBQ near me and this place came up. I called them and spoke to a super patient woman on the phone that explained their menu and took my order. When I got to the establishment the customer service got even better. Super friendly staff. They brought me my meal to the car. The food was delicious. It is like a Texas BBQ and the sauce is so good. I got brisket, chicken, and ribs. She warned me about the kids loving the cornbread muffins and she was right. They tried to take mine. Everything was so good. Portions were OK but still worth it. They will definitely see me again.

Living nearby, West Side BBQ has become a staple of my wife and my "we're too lazy to drive somewhere" dinner plans in very short time.  Portions are generous and the service is very friendly.  It's BYOB!  A great place to sit outside on a warmer day (inside gets a bit too hot during the summer as it's not air conditioned).  We've done take out a few times and loved it.  They need a website for easier ordering and so that their menu is online.  Food: Generally very good to excellent, but not world class (not that I would expect world-class at this price point!).  The BBQ sauce used (there appears to be at least two different types) is more towards the tangy end and is very good, but not perfect.  Brisket was very good, Ribs were excellent (less tangy), sweet potato fries are amazing.  The Nachos appetizer is very large and excellent.  I haven't experienced enough of Worcester yet to say for sure, but I have a feeling this place is in contention for best BBQ in the city.  I would rate it very favorably compared to most of the BBQ places I was familiar with in Boston (recently moved).  Atmosphere: Most seating during the summer is outside on the front patio.  It can get a bit loud as Pleasant St. is fairly busy, but the neighborhood is nice and conversation is still easy.  Occasionally, some people smoking at the nearby coffee shop have caused some annoyance (smoke drifting over).  Inside has a couple of booths and a TV.  I've never eaten inside, but it seems like it would be nice, albeit with less atmosphere, when the weather dictates indoor eating.  Note: there is a nearby liquor store which has chilled wine/beer for sale at non-crazy prices.
